{"updated_at": {"date": {"d": "13", "m": "11", "Y": "2025"}, "time": {"H": "22", "M": "10", "S": "25"}}, "news": [{"title": "Delhi civic body to install CCTV cameras at 524 spots to tackle construction dumping", "para": "The Municipal Corporation of Delhi (MCD) is installing CCTV cameras at 524 locations to combat illegal dumping of construction and demolition waste. This initiative aims to identify and penalize habitual offenders, complementing existing designated dumping sites and processing plants. The city generates substantial C&D waste daily, with efforts underway to increase processing capacity and improve waste management infrastructure.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/infrastructure/mcd-to-combat-construction-waste-524-cctv-cameras-to-be-installed-in-delhi/125293965?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-93654/125293965.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "infrastructure"}, {"title": "ED arrests ex-MD of Jaypee Infratech in \u20b914,599 crore 'scam' case", "para": "In a significant move, the Enforcement Directorate apprehended Manoj Gaur, the former Managing Director of Jaypee Infratech, as part of a massive fraud investigation concerning \u20b914,599 crore. This scandal involves the misuse of funds intended for housing projects, with allegations that home buyers' investments were misappropriated. ", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/regulatory/ed-arrests-ex-md-of-jaypee-infratech-in-14599-crore-scam-case/125297542?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-29320/125297542.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "regulatory"}, {"title": "Sub-registrar, realtor arrested in land-grab case in Bengaluru", "para": "Bengaluru CCB sleuths have arrested a sub-registrar and a realtor-cum-middleman in a land-grab case involving forged documents and the sale of multiple residential sites without the landowner's knowledge. The August 2022 case, initially filed at Parappana Agrahara police station, has led to the arrest of approximately 100 suspects so far.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/regulatory/sub-registrar-and-realtor-arrested-in-major-bengaluru-land-grabbing-scandal/125293915?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-32062/125293915.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "regulatory"}]}